msContents.summary: Nearly complete copy of the book of Bahāʼ Allah with interlinear Persian translation; copy is missing the final line.

supportDesc.extent: ii, 124, ii leaves : 178 x 110 (115 x 78) mm, bound to 183 x 120 x 22 mm

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 16 long lines; 8 Arabic, 8 Persian translation.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh in black ink and nastaʻlīq in red ink; pointed.

binding.p: Green and black marbled paper sides over cardboard; red spine.

origin.p: The item is undated, text and translation probably copied between 1874 and 1877.

history.provenance: Formerly owned by Rev. James Bassett, given to him in Tehran in 1877 (note in ink, f. 1r).
